author: Mick Gadd
title: FA Cup 4th round draw in full - Non-league Sutton and Lincoln join Crystal Palace and Burnley in next chapter
text:
Get daily   Thank you for subscribing!   
Non-league Sutton United and Lincoln City reached the FA Cup's fourth round in thrilling fashion, both scoring at the death against more fancied opposition. 
Lincoln beat Ipswich 1-0 to win a berth against Brighton and Sutton overran AFC Wimbledon 3-1 for a spot against Leeds. 
Barnsley scored in stoppage time of extra-time to win their clash with Blackburn. 
They join Tuesday's other winners Burnley, Bristol City, Crystal Palace and Blackpool. 
Manchester United will face Wigan, with boss Warren Joyce getting a chance at taking on his former club. Roarie Deacon celebrates Sutton's first goal (Photo: Getty Images Europe) (Photo: REUTERS) 
Chelsea are facing neighbours Brentford while Leicester travel the short distance to high-flying Derby for an all-East Midlands encounter. 
Lincoln's reward would be a home clash with Championship promotion chasers Brighton. 
Chelsea will face Brentford in a west-London derby at Stamford Bridge while Pep Guardiola's Manchester City travel to face either Crystal Palace or Bolton. 
Middlesbrough face a potential banana skin at home to Accrington Stanley, who won on their last visit to Teesside. Christian aid: Benteke bailed Palace out (Photo: Ian Walton) Sam Vokes celebrates his opening goal (Photo: Richard Heathcote) 
The winners of the replay between Plymouth and Liverpool tomorrow night will face Wolves, who pulled off one of the biggest shocks in round three with their win at Stoke. 
The FA Cup's fourth round fixtures will be played on the weekend commencing January 28. FULL FA CUP 4TH ROUND DRAW (Tuesday's replay winners in bold)
